1
00:03:24,571 --> 00:03:26,490
Hello, guys!

2
00:03:26,490 --> 00:03:29,251
It's our first day and
here are the cleaners.

3
00:03:29,263 --> 00:03:30,319
Hello!

4
00:03:30,343 --> 00:03:31,711
Say hello to the camera!

5
00:03:31,735 --> 00:03:34,070
See, you guys are
great at cleaning.

6
00:03:34,094 --> 00:03:35,674
Oh, Felice!

7
00:03:35,698 --> 00:03:36,892
What’s going on?

8
00:03:37,315 --> 00:03:38,995
My pouch is missing

9
00:03:39,019 --> 00:03:40,611
and my money’s in there.

10
00:03:41,185 --> 00:03:42,311
Oh, no!

11
00:03:42,696 --> 00:03:44,432
Maybe it was stolen by…

12
00:03:47,032 --> 00:03:48,266
What's wrong with you?

13
00:03:48,290 --> 00:03:49,646
It's not funny.

14
00:03:55,898 --> 00:03:57,025
What’s her problem?

15
00:03:57,304 --> 00:03:59,781
They're cleaning right now.

16
00:03:59,805 --> 00:04:02,301
[students screaming]

17
00:04:02,325 --> 00:04:03,325
Wah!

18
00:04:03,330 --> 00:04:05,290
Bet you were scared.

19
00:04:06,149 --> 00:04:07,171
Come on.

20
00:04:07,196 --> 00:04:08,196
What?

21
00:04:08,220 --> 00:04:10,122
I'm vlogging and-

22
00:04:10,146 --> 00:04:12,195
- You're crazy, Santiago.
- So what?

23
00:04:12,219 --> 00:04:15,464
- You all are losers.
-There.

24
00:04:15,488 --> 00:04:16,506
And there.

25
00:04:16,531 --> 00:04:18,833
And then...

26
00:04:19,474 --> 00:04:24,084
[students screaming]

27
00:06:02,687 --> 00:06:05,857
I’m not used to Moma not
being the first one I hear

28
00:06:06,203 --> 00:06:10,207
waking me up on the first day of
my last year as a high school student.

29
00:06:18,314 --> 00:06:21,607
Oh no! I think I fell
asleep in my uniform.

30
00:06:35,122 --> 00:06:37,469
I think I really need
to clean my room.

31
00:06:40,910 --> 00:06:41,910
Mom?

32
00:06:43,714 --> 00:06:44,714
Moma?

33
00:06:49,795 --> 00:06:51,138
Ah...

34
00:06:51,138 --> 00:06:55,540
Mom must have left at dawn
to sell her yema and rice cakes.

35
00:07:24,213 --> 00:07:26,786
I've had so many first days
in junior high already.

36
00:07:27,312 --> 00:07:30,405
But I don't know,
I still get nervous.

37
00:07:43,881 --> 00:07:44,881
MOANA "THIEF"

38
00:07:44,906 --> 00:07:48,384
This is so annoying,
they still won't leave me alone.

39
00:07:59,462 --> 00:08:00,964
Oh!

40
00:08:01,523 --> 00:08:04,546
I thought you were brave!

41
00:08:04,569 --> 00:08:05,611
You're such a jerk.

42
00:08:06,587 --> 00:08:08,572
- Let's go.
- Should we go back to the classroom?

43
00:08:16,691 --> 00:08:18,568
Oh, look, it’s Felice.

44
00:08:19,209 --> 00:08:22,838
She’s probably coming from early morning
practice again with the school band.

45
00:08:23,897 --> 00:08:25,190
She’s so beautiful.

46
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,967
Being a majorette
really suits Felice.

47
00:08:29,310 --> 00:08:32,105
I would also like to
join our school band.

48
00:08:32,638 --> 00:08:34,514
Not as a majorette, though.

49
00:08:34,539 --> 00:08:37,600
Since I’m not as beautiful
or as sexy as Felice.

50
00:08:38,218 --> 00:08:40,637
What I really want
is to be a lyrist.

51
00:08:41,179 --> 00:08:43,223
But Moma is against it

52
00:08:43,473 --> 00:08:44,808
she says it’s just
a waste of money.

53
00:08:48,092 --> 00:08:49,718
What’s happening to her?

54
00:08:50,782 --> 00:08:52,075
Should I go over there?

55
00:08:58,195 --> 00:08:59,195
Felice.

56
00:09:20,717 --> 00:09:23,187
- Did you do your homework?
- Are you done with yours?

57
00:09:23,211 --> 00:09:24,741
- No we didn't.
- Not yet but we'll do it later.

58
00:09:24,765 --> 00:09:27,491
I'm sorry guys but im done with mine,
you should finish yours too.

59
00:09:38,369 --> 00:09:39,891
Oh, it's just the wind.

60
00:09:55,511 --> 00:09:56,687
Felice!

61
00:09:56,711 --> 00:09:57,879
Let’s sit together.

62
00:09:59,404 --> 00:10:02,490
Felice, come here!

63
00:10:07,143 --> 00:10:08,561
Are we having an acitivity?

64
00:10:09,567 --> 00:10:10,860
I don’t know.

65
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:13,943
Good morning, class.

66
00:10:14,603 --> 00:10:17,940
Good morning, Sir Win.

67
00:10:19,285 --> 00:10:20,609
I'm sorry, class.

68
00:10:21,508 --> 00:10:23,372
There was an accident.

69
00:10:24,414 --> 00:10:25,665
On the way here

70
00:10:25,690 --> 00:10:26,775
someone got hit.

71
00:10:27,233 --> 00:10:29,527
Did the person die, Sir Win?

72
00:10:30,083 --> 00:10:31,298
I think so.

73
00:10:34,084 --> 00:10:35,668
Sadly, she was on her phone

74
00:10:35,668 --> 00:10:37,386
when the accident happened.

75
00:10:38,129 --> 00:10:41,092
So, everyone, please,
when crossing the road

76
00:10:41,116 --> 00:10:42,868
This is just a reminder, okay?

77
00:10:42,868 --> 00:10:44,685
But it’s super effective always.

78
00:10:44,709 --> 00:10:47,055
When crossing the road,
look to your left…

79
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,690
Look to your right.

80
00:10:48,714 --> 00:10:50,177
Very nice, good.

81
00:10:50,201 --> 00:10:51,568
You know what, class

82
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:58,241
Science tells us that the very last sense
that stops functioning before we die

83
00:10:58,522 --> 00:10:59,898
is the sense of hearing.

84
00:11:01,288 --> 00:11:04,083
Whoever it is that
she was talking to

85
00:11:05,278 --> 00:11:07,030
I hope it was someone she loves.

86
00:11:07,906 --> 00:11:09,366
And the last word she heard,

87
00:11:09,366 --> 00:11:11,201
I hope they were kind.

88
00:11:11,701 --> 00:11:12,701
Right.

89
00:11:13,286 --> 00:11:14,621
Alright, um…

90
00:11:17,509 --> 00:11:22,139
Later we'll have an activity.

91
00:11:24,795 --> 00:11:27,631
This is just a review from
last year's lessons.

92
00:11:28,022 --> 00:11:29,022
Alright?

93
00:11:47,034 --> 00:11:48,034
[knocking]

94
00:11:51,191 --> 00:11:52,484
Hello, everyone.

95
00:11:52,484 --> 00:11:54,784
I am Cadet Officer Dylan Gallego.

96
00:11:54,808 --> 00:11:56,298
And I just want
to remind you guys

97
00:11:56,322 --> 00:11:59,594
that we have an anti-bullying seminar
happening in 10 minutes.

98
00:12:00,499 --> 00:12:02,167
Attendance is a must.

99
00:12:03,229 --> 00:12:05,133
Okay, you may go.

100
00:12:10,390 --> 00:12:13,065
Sir, can I be excused?

101
00:12:14,282 --> 00:12:16,450
I already attended
the same seminar

102
00:12:16,475 --> 00:12:18,287
as part of our training
for the school band.

103
00:12:18,311 --> 00:12:21,949
Maybe I can use the time
to rest for the meantime.

104
00:12:23,596 --> 00:12:24,794
Alright.

105
00:12:24,818 --> 00:12:26,018
You can rest here, Felice.

106
00:12:26,588 --> 00:12:27,672
Thank you.

107
00:13:08,379 --> 00:13:10,632
Hey, Naomi.
What are you doing?

108
00:13:12,583 --> 00:13:15,211
No wonder things are
going missing around here.

109
00:13:17,189 --> 00:13:19,441
You’re a thief!

110
00:13:37,187 --> 00:13:38,730
Where have you been?

111
00:13:46,589 --> 00:13:48,007
How snobbish.

112
00:13:48,689 --> 00:13:50,107
What is happening?

113
00:14:01,412 --> 00:14:05,070
It's our first day and
here are the cleaners.

114
00:14:05,094 --> 00:14:06,679
It was just here.

115
00:14:07,790 --> 00:14:09,449
Where is it?

116
00:14:09,473 --> 00:14:13,107
Hi cleaners! Go ahead and clean.

117
00:14:15,288 --> 00:14:16,789
Oh, Felice!

118
00:14:16,814 --> 00:14:18,066
What’s going on?

119
00:14:18,090 --> 00:14:19,501
My pouch is missing

120
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:21,277
and my money’s in there.

121
00:14:21,761 --> 00:14:23,495
Felice! It was Naomi!

122
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:25,480
Naomi stole your pouch!

123
00:14:25,504 --> 00:14:26,657
Oh my!

124
00:14:26,681 --> 00:14:28,367
Maybe it was stolen by…

125
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,078
What's wrong with you?

126
00:14:31,102 --> 00:14:32,336
That's not funny.

127
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:34,913
There you go,
we're tidying up  first–

128
00:14:36,077 --> 00:14:37,495
What’s her problem?

129
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,418
I think she's upset.

130
00:14:39,974 --> 00:14:41,642
Such an attention seeker.

131
00:14:42,213 --> 00:14:44,693
[students screaming]

132
00:14:44,717 --> 00:14:46,220
- Waah!
- Felice, it was Naomi!

133
00:14:46,244 --> 00:14:47,488
Are you mad?

134
00:14:47,512 --> 00:14:48,781
Did I do something wrong?

135
00:14:48,805 --> 00:14:51,009
Felice, why aren’t
you listening to me?

136
00:14:51,033 --> 00:14:52,162
Felice!

137
00:14:56,938 --> 00:14:57,938
Felice!

138
00:14:57,963 --> 00:15:00,340
[screaming continues]

139
00:15:33,976 --> 00:15:36,354
Why are they mean to me?

140
00:15:45,084 --> 00:15:46,362
Who’s that?

141
00:15:48,005 --> 00:15:49,048
Are you okay?

142
00:15:51,786 --> 00:15:54,912
I've been trying to talk to you,
but you were ignoring me.

143
00:15:54,936 --> 00:15:57,123
And now you suddenly
want to talk?

144
00:16:32,742 --> 00:16:34,285
Oh, it's just the wind.

145
00:16:34,309 --> 00:16:35,328
Felice!

146
00:16:35,352 --> 00:16:36,454
Let’s sit together.

147
00:16:36,478 --> 00:16:38,248
You’re a thief.

148
00:16:38,272 --> 00:16:39,582
Where have you been?

149
00:16:43,628 --> 00:16:45,338
No!

150
00:16:48,086 --> 00:16:49,086
No.

151
00:17:18,407 --> 00:17:19,658
No!

152
00:17:21,501 --> 00:17:24,689
This isn’t real.

153
00:17:31,029 --> 00:17:32,468
This isn’t real.

154
00:18:35,406 --> 00:18:38,242
Moma, you totally startled me!

155
00:18:38,242 --> 00:18:40,369
Hey, you're the one
who startled me!

156
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:42,705
Why did you wake up so early?

157
00:18:56,410 --> 00:18:59,247
Of course, we now have
a beauty routine, Moma.

158
00:19:00,023 --> 00:19:03,901
You know, my pretty classmates
at school use that.

159
00:19:03,934 --> 00:19:05,266
Look at my skin, Moma.

160
00:19:05,290 --> 00:19:06,729
- It’s glowing now.
- Let me look.

161
00:19:06,888 --> 00:19:08,371
Oh, wow. You’re right!

162
00:19:08,843 --> 00:19:12,891
Why is my daughter suddenly
so motivated to look pretty?

163
00:19:16,051 --> 00:19:17,302
Well, that's just how it is.

164
00:19:17,855 --> 00:19:19,065
I’m all grown up now.

165
00:19:20,203 --> 00:19:21,637
I guess this means
you won't want to come

166
00:19:21,661 --> 00:19:23,454
with me to our spot
at the market anymore.

167
00:19:23,478 --> 00:19:26,291
So what’s going to happen
to our yema and rice cakes?

168
00:19:26,937 --> 00:19:28,543
That's not going to happen.

169
00:19:28,981 --> 00:19:31,039
That’s exactly why
I use White Rose Papaya.

170
00:19:31,063 --> 00:19:35,609
So even if I’m out in the sun or sweating,
my skin still stays glowing.

171
00:19:37,696 --> 00:19:40,199
You're definitely the prettiest
girl in your school.

172
00:19:40,598 --> 00:19:42,224
You take after me, after all.

173
00:19:49,206 --> 00:19:50,206
This isn’t real.

174
00:19:51,299 --> 00:19:53,009
This isn’t real.

175
00:20:23,081 --> 00:20:24,332
Moana.

176
00:20:25,814 --> 00:20:27,816
Was that you I felt earlier?

177
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:30,480
Yes.

178
00:20:31,030 --> 00:20:32,030
Yes, Felice.

179
00:20:32,054 --> 00:20:35,169
That was me.
I’m here, Felice.

180
00:20:37,979 --> 00:20:39,772
I really hope it was you.

181
00:20:40,715 --> 00:20:44,702
Because I really need a friend now.

182
00:20:48,228 --> 00:20:50,584
- Bye, you guys take care.
- Bye, Moana.

183
00:20:50,608 --> 00:20:51,876
Bye!

184
00:20:51,901 --> 00:20:53,211
What a day!

185
00:20:54,837 --> 00:20:56,339
Are we going to commute?

186
00:21:20,613 --> 00:21:21,823
So dramatic.

187
00:21:24,310 --> 00:21:26,825
Oh, I’m sorry!
Give me your hand.

188
00:21:27,495 --> 00:21:28,496
Sit down.

189
00:21:31,082 --> 00:21:34,586
This is what my mom does to me
whenever I get panic attacks.

190
00:21:40,085 --> 00:21:41,795
Are you feeling better now?

191
00:21:47,599 --> 00:21:48,809
I’m okay now.

192
00:22:01,493 --> 00:22:03,036
You must be really tired.

193
00:22:04,475 --> 00:22:07,410
You just came from practice,
didn't you?

194
00:22:07,789 --> 00:22:08,789
Yes, I did.

195
00:22:10,079 --> 00:22:12,081
Sir Jonas is merciless.
Did you know?

196
00:22:12,081 --> 00:22:15,752
My arms are like Jello from
twirling that baton all day.

197
00:22:16,294 --> 00:22:17,587
I’m so tired, friend.

198
00:22:29,812 --> 00:22:30,812
What’s that?

199
00:22:31,893 --> 00:22:32,977
Yema candy.

200
00:22:33,394 --> 00:22:34,394
It’s for you.

201
00:22:36,356 --> 00:22:37,919
To give you an energy boost.

202
00:22:39,193 --> 00:22:40,193
Here.

203
00:22:43,822 --> 00:22:45,073
Don’t worry.

204
00:22:45,073 --> 00:22:48,117
My mom used healthy sugar,
so it’s not fattening.

205
00:22:48,701 --> 00:22:49,952
That exists?

206
00:22:51,523 --> 00:22:52,750
Just believe me.

207
00:22:53,477 --> 00:22:55,354
Alright, if you say so.

208
00:23:03,308 --> 00:23:04,434
It’s good, right?

209
00:23:06,409 --> 00:23:07,409
You know,

210
00:23:07,783 --> 00:23:10,609
Moma’s hands look
like Christmas lights now

211
00:23:10,633 --> 00:23:12,260
with all the wrapping
she does with those yemas.

212
00:23:12,897 --> 00:23:14,106
You’re so crazy.

213
00:23:14,624 --> 00:23:15,709
It’s true.

214
00:23:16,001 --> 00:23:19,504
The color from the cellophane
has already stained her fingers.

215
00:23:21,923 --> 00:23:26,553
But that doesn’t mean
Moma doesn’t wash her hands.

216
00:23:26,553 --> 00:23:28,597
- For sure.
- Her yema is clean.

217
00:23:28,597 --> 00:23:30,640
It’s just the color from the wrappers
that got on her hands.

218
00:23:31,224 --> 00:23:32,267
Yeah, for sure.

219
00:23:34,936 --> 00:23:36,605
Your mom really loves you,
doesn’t she?

220
00:23:37,522 --> 00:23:38,607
She really does.

221
00:23:39,893 --> 00:23:41,144
We’re a team.

222
00:23:41,589 --> 00:23:44,882
We’re Moma and Momay.

223
00:23:47,103 --> 00:23:49,564
Oh, Moma.

224
00:23:50,294 --> 00:23:52,755
Monica Marie.
That’s her name.

225
00:23:53,305 --> 00:23:55,704
Momay is short for Moana Marie.

226
00:23:55,728 --> 00:23:59,397
That’s why I call
her Moma—it just fits.

227
00:24:02,164 --> 00:24:04,708
You know, I love her so much,
even if she is a total killjoy.

228
00:24:05,271 --> 00:24:06,271
Killjoy?

229
00:24:07,059 --> 00:24:08,059
Yeah.

230
00:24:08,727 --> 00:24:11,521
She doesn’t want me
to join the marching band.

231
00:24:11,521 --> 00:24:12,648
She says it’s just
a waste of money

232
00:24:13,188 --> 00:24:15,816
So you want to
be a majorette too?

233
00:24:15,816 --> 00:24:18,735
Then we’d both have aching arms.

234
00:24:19,194 --> 00:24:20,194
Crazy.

235
00:24:20,612 --> 00:24:24,032
I want to be a lyrist.
I’m not as pretty as you.

236
00:24:25,016 --> 00:24:26,225
You’re pretty, too.

237
00:24:29,496 --> 00:24:30,706
Thank you.

238
00:24:32,183 --> 00:24:33,183
So, yeah.

239
00:24:33,584 --> 00:24:37,671
You can call me Momay ‘cause
Moana Marie’s too long.

240
00:24:38,715 --> 00:24:43,971
Or you can call me
Moana thief.

241
00:24:43,971 --> 00:24:44,971
Crazy!

242
00:24:45,727 --> 00:24:51,448
Because that’s what
our classmates call me.

243
00:24:52,381 --> 00:24:53,716
They’re calling me a klepto.

244
00:24:54,286 --> 00:24:55,615
And apparently,

245
00:24:55,639 --> 00:24:59,184
I’m being blamed for all
the recent thefts in our class.

246
00:25:00,810 --> 00:25:02,771
I don’t believe that.

247
00:25:04,032 --> 00:25:05,932
- Why?
- I just know.

248
00:25:07,145 --> 00:25:10,356
Also, this is just between us,

249
00:25:11,898 --> 00:25:13,900
Even if we don’t
talk all the time,

250
00:25:14,192 --> 00:25:15,735
I feel so at ease with you.

251
00:25:16,319 --> 00:25:21,908
I just know, deep down,
that you're someone I can count on.

252
00:25:23,284 --> 00:25:24,689
So there’s no need to overthink.

253
00:25:24,713 --> 00:25:27,632
Not everyone believes in rumors.

254
00:25:30,199 --> 00:25:31,951
Oh, wow.

255
00:25:32,368 --> 00:25:33,368
You’re being so dramatic.

256
00:25:40,205 --> 00:25:41,873
Come on, let’s go home.

257
00:25:51,759 --> 00:25:52,802
Moana.

258
00:25:53,094 --> 00:25:54,553
Moana!

259
00:25:58,284 --> 00:26:00,411
I’m so sorry, Momay.

260
00:26:02,830 --> 00:26:04,248
Don't worry,

261
00:26:05,984 --> 00:26:08,612
I’ll always visit your mom
in the hospital.

262
00:26:10,486 --> 00:26:11,486
Hospital?

263
00:26:15,324 --> 00:26:16,993
What happened to Moma?

264
00:26:19,396 --> 00:26:21,773
I’m so so sorry.

265
00:26:26,168 --> 00:26:27,168
Felice.

266
00:26:27,169 --> 00:26:28,504
Are you avoiding me?

267
00:26:28,829 --> 00:26:30,047
Of course not!

268
00:26:30,389 --> 00:26:32,734
Why are you being so dramatic?
What’s your problem?

269
00:26:32,758 --> 00:26:33,865
Seriously?

270
00:26:33,889 --> 00:26:35,622
Why are you avoiding me, Felice?

271
00:26:36,136 --> 00:26:38,472
Dylan, stop it.
You’re hurting me.

272
00:26:38,496 --> 00:26:40,557
Hey, don't you dare touch Felice!

273
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:18,800
Sorry.

274
00:27:22,300 --> 00:27:23,300
Come in.

275
00:27:23,607 --> 00:27:28,396
I am so sorry.
I think I interrupted your practice.

276
00:27:28,888 --> 00:27:31,191
Don’t worry,
I wasn’t practicing.

277
00:27:31,803 --> 00:27:33,305
I’m not part of the marching band.

278
00:27:34,373 --> 00:27:35,373
Sit down.

279
00:27:36,292 --> 00:27:37,697
But you’re actually really good.

280
00:27:39,420 --> 00:27:40,420
I know.

281
00:27:46,260 --> 00:27:47,260
You see,

282
00:27:48,679 --> 00:27:52,183
I can see and hear
every single note.

283
00:27:53,309 --> 00:27:57,271
I guess that’s why playing any
instrument comes so easily to me.

284
00:27:58,418 --> 00:28:00,754
Oh, so you’re a musician?

285
00:28:01,798 --> 00:28:02,798
Actually, no.

286
00:28:03,703 --> 00:28:04,703
I’m a cadet.

287
00:28:05,581 --> 00:28:07,750
I’m here because
I’m waiting for my girlfriend.

288
00:28:08,488 --> 00:28:09,739
She’s a majorette.

289
00:28:10,606 --> 00:28:12,671
She’s very lucky, then.

290
00:28:13,908 --> 00:28:14,908
I know.

291
00:28:15,878 --> 00:28:21,592
It’s also my dream to be part of
the marching band as a lyrist.

292
00:28:22,014 --> 00:28:23,349
But Moma is against it.

293
00:28:23,349 --> 00:28:24,559
She says it’s just
a waste of money.

294
00:28:25,696 --> 00:28:28,908
You know what,
you shouldn’t listen to your mom.

295
00:28:32,989 --> 00:28:36,048
Because for me,
it’s just a waste of time.

296
00:28:38,906 --> 00:28:43,744
Everything that they say or do
is just a reflection of their insecurities.

297
00:28:45,079 --> 00:28:46,873
I don’t think it’s like that.

298
00:28:47,398 --> 00:28:49,025
Trust me, that's how it is.

299
00:28:51,085 --> 00:28:55,631
Is your mom against you
focusing on music, too?

300
00:28:59,820 --> 00:29:02,823
To be honest,
I wouldn’t know.

301
00:29:04,015 --> 00:29:08,311
Because I was young
when she left us.

302
00:29:09,937 --> 00:29:10,937
Oh...

303
00:29:11,812 --> 00:29:12,813
I’m sorry to hear that.

304
00:29:13,212 --> 00:29:18,759
That’s why I didn’t pursue music.
It was because of her.

305
00:29:20,714 --> 00:29:23,971
Is that why you just want
to join the military instead?

306
00:29:25,427 --> 00:29:26,427
Exactly.

307
00:29:27,591 --> 00:29:29,092
Do you want me to teach you?

308
00:29:29,908 --> 00:29:30,908
Really?

309
00:29:30,933 --> 00:29:32,643
Yes, I will teach you. Here.

310
00:29:33,018 --> 00:29:34,228
Right now?

311
00:29:34,228 --> 00:29:35,979
Of course, right now.
When else would it be?

312
00:29:37,715 --> 00:29:38,758
This is just simple.

313
00:29:41,094 --> 00:29:42,094
Here.

314
00:29:43,253 --> 00:29:44,466
But it's already late.

315
00:29:44,491 --> 00:29:46,323
Maybe we can
just do it next time?

316
00:29:47,783 --> 00:29:50,911
You know what,
time is gold.

317
00:29:52,297 --> 00:29:55,425
There might not be a next time.

318
00:29:56,917 --> 00:29:58,043
Or maybe…

319
00:29:59,812 --> 00:30:02,842
You'll be the one
who's gone by then.

320
00:30:07,472 --> 00:30:08,747
I really can't.

321
00:30:08,771 --> 00:30:10,346
Moma will get really mad at me.

322
00:30:10,347 --> 00:30:13,395
Didn't I tell you?
Stop listening to your mother.

323
00:30:13,803 --> 00:30:17,098
Because she doesn't want you
to achieve what she never could.

324
00:30:17,813 --> 00:30:20,416
Moma is not like that.

325
00:30:20,440 --> 00:30:21,817
You listen to me.

326
00:30:25,946 --> 00:30:29,157
So, you’re going
to listen to me now?

327
00:30:31,217 --> 00:30:32,217
Sit down.

328
00:30:34,824 --> 00:30:35,824
Sit down.

329
00:30:40,316 --> 00:30:42,068
Help me!

330
00:30:43,733 --> 00:30:44,921
Don't make this difficult!

331
00:30:46,153 --> 00:30:47,742
I’m begging you...
please don't.

332
00:30:47,766 --> 00:30:49,030
Please, don’t.

333
00:30:49,030 --> 00:30:50,974
I’m begging you...
please don't.

334
00:30:51,954 --> 00:30:54,102
I’m begging you...
please don't.

335
00:31:08,241 --> 00:31:09,241
Goddammit!

336
00:31:47,968 --> 00:31:51,555
I’m done with this world.
I’m sorry for everything.

337
00:32:21,734 --> 00:32:23,778
Please stay calm, Felice.

338
00:32:32,277 --> 00:32:35,954
Don’t worry, I won't let
anything happen to you.

339
00:33:19,172 --> 00:33:20,172
Felice.

340
00:33:21,098 --> 00:33:22,307
Felice, he’s gone.

341
00:33:25,128 --> 00:33:26,337
Felice.

342
00:33:28,029 --> 00:33:29,029
Felice.

343
00:33:33,783 --> 00:33:35,493
I’m in Felice’s body.

344
00:34:36,584 --> 00:34:37,584
Mom.

345
00:34:40,781 --> 00:34:42,325
I’m sorry, mom.

346
00:34:44,787 --> 00:34:45,955
I’m sorry.

347
00:34:48,188 --> 00:34:50,505
This is not your fault, Moma.

348
00:34:55,388 --> 00:34:56,931
Because I know now.

349
00:34:58,986 --> 00:35:02,072
I know I didn’t kill myself.

350
00:35:03,801 --> 00:35:05,353
I could never do that to you.

351
00:35:05,378 --> 00:35:09,524
Because more than anything,
I can't bear to hurt you.

352
00:35:11,475 --> 00:35:13,519
I can't leave you alone.

353
00:35:16,733 --> 00:35:20,452
Don't let go. Just hold on, Moma.

354
00:35:33,584 --> 00:35:37,213
I won't stop until
I get justice for myself.

355
00:35:45,678 --> 00:35:47,763
I’m getting my revenge.

356
00:35:51,166 --> 00:35:52,834
I will get justice for you, Moma.

357
00:35:55,973 --> 00:35:59,073
I will find justice for myself.

358
00:36:00,320 --> 00:36:02,655
I’m going to do exactly
what he did to me.

359
00:36:03,715 --> 00:36:06,933
I’ll kill him in the very spot
where he killed me.

360
00:36:06,957 --> 00:36:08,166
That’s a promise.

361
00:36:14,112 --> 00:36:16,155
I just want you to live, Mom.

362
00:36:19,102 --> 00:36:20,145
Happy.

363
00:36:22,097 --> 00:36:24,099
Without carrying heavy burdens.

364
00:36:30,063 --> 00:36:31,063
[phone chimes]

365
00:36:39,006 --> 00:36:40,091
Where are you?

366
00:36:40,657 --> 00:36:41,657
Let’s talk.

367
00:36:50,309 --> 00:36:53,989
You know how an AI video
can ruin someone’s reputation.

368
00:36:54,520 --> 00:36:58,007
Meet me,
or I’ll start spreading it.

369
00:37:05,003 --> 00:37:06,724
Meet me at school.

370
00:37:07,684 --> 00:37:08,977
Wait for me.

371
00:37:51,799 --> 00:37:55,219
Does this sound familiar to you, Gallego?

372
00:37:57,796 --> 00:37:59,247
Felice, about a while ago.

373
00:38:00,570 --> 00:38:01,570
I’m sorry.

374
00:38:10,594 --> 00:38:14,306
Did you feel even a
shred of pity for your victim?

375
00:38:15,486 --> 00:38:17,988
Dammit, Felice!
What the hell are you talking about?

376
00:38:18,494 --> 00:38:19,715
You’ve been acting
like this all day.

377
00:38:19,740 --> 00:38:24,260
I know you did it, you monster!

378
00:38:24,886 --> 00:38:26,304
You did all of this on purpose.

379
00:38:27,299 --> 00:38:29,391
You faked that suicide note.

380
00:38:29,415 --> 00:38:31,578
You even made sure
I was the one who came here,

381
00:38:31,602 --> 00:38:33,561
so that I’d be the one
to discover her body.

382
00:38:33,880 --> 00:38:35,882
You planned every single bit of it.

383
00:38:37,397 --> 00:38:41,860
Now tell me,
did you ever feel sorry for me?

384
00:38:44,191 --> 00:38:45,615
Do you want to know the truth?

385
00:38:47,368 --> 00:38:48,368
No.

386
00:38:49,503 --> 00:38:50,837
I don't feel any pity.

387
00:38:52,377 --> 00:38:54,504
You want to know who I pity?

388
00:38:55,700 --> 00:38:57,619
I pity myself, Felice.

389
00:38:58,392 --> 00:38:59,810
Because I’m going
to end up behind bars.

390
00:39:01,192 --> 00:39:04,384
Look at me—
I’m Dylan fucking Gallego.

391
00:39:05,009 --> 00:39:06,997
And I’m going to jail
because of one little problem.

392
00:39:07,021 --> 00:39:08,388
One mistake.

393
00:39:09,705 --> 00:39:11,874
I am the future General
of the Philippines.

394
00:39:12,295 --> 00:39:15,381
And if I wanted to be,
the future President.

395
00:39:16,404 --> 00:39:17,697
And I’m supposed
to just go to jail?

396
00:39:18,782 --> 00:39:24,454
So much potential wasted in this world
because of one stupid mistake.

397
00:39:25,298 --> 00:39:32,670
I won't let my life be destroyed.
I will not let one mistake derail my life.

398
00:39:32,694 --> 00:39:34,641
That wasn't just
a simple mistake.

399
00:39:34,665 --> 00:39:35,665
You killed...

400
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:37,376
You killed her.

401
00:39:37,376 --> 00:39:39,479
- I accidentally killed her.
- You killed her.

402
00:39:39,504 --> 00:39:42,256
Okay, fine. I killed her.

403
00:39:44,532 --> 00:39:46,158
But let me ask you this

404
00:39:47,696 --> 00:39:49,323
Do you even remember her name?

405
00:39:51,802 --> 00:39:54,930
Did you even consider her a friend?

406
00:40:00,881 --> 00:40:02,174
Exactly my point.

407
00:40:03,008 --> 00:40:05,135
She’s a nobody, Felice.

408
00:40:06,095 --> 00:40:10,057
She will be easily forgotten.
An invisible girl.

409
00:40:21,986 --> 00:40:23,696
Thank you for understanding, babe.

410
00:40:24,708 --> 00:40:26,418
I knew you’d understand me.

411
00:40:28,993 --> 00:40:33,706
I know whatever happens,
you’ll support me.

412
00:40:35,791 --> 00:40:37,001
Momay.

413
00:40:38,711 --> 00:40:39,711
Huh?

414
00:40:40,299 --> 00:40:42,301
My name is Moana Marie.

415
00:40:42,898 --> 00:40:43,898
What?

416
00:41:05,811 --> 00:41:07,313
No, Momay!

417
00:41:08,296 --> 00:41:10,214
Momay, don’t do it.

418
00:41:14,719 --> 00:41:16,494
I heard you earlier.

419
00:41:17,891 --> 00:41:20,977
You mentioned killing
the person who killed you.

420
00:41:22,585 --> 00:41:25,108
In the same place you were killed.

421
00:41:26,996 --> 00:41:27,996
Here.

422
00:41:30,485 --> 00:41:35,323
I know it was you who spoke to me
when I wanted to let go

423
00:41:36,491 --> 00:41:38,952
You told me to keep fighting.

424
00:41:40,098 --> 00:41:44,186
That’s why I knew
I had to wake up and live.

425
00:41:47,113 --> 00:41:49,157
But he has to pay, Moma.

426
00:41:50,420 --> 00:41:53,966
He stole my life and dreams for us.

427
00:41:54,404 --> 00:41:58,659
But you don’t have to do
to him what he did to you.

428
00:42:00,299 --> 00:42:02,093
I know you’re a good person.

429
00:42:04,296 --> 00:42:06,090
Because you’re my daughter.

430
00:42:10,302 --> 00:42:12,262
I raised you.

431
00:42:15,799 --> 00:42:16,967
And in the end,

432
00:42:18,820 --> 00:42:22,532
what’s important
is how you lived,

433
00:42:23,495 --> 00:42:25,080
not how you died.

434
00:42:31,371 --> 00:42:32,581
I’m sorry, Moma.

435
00:42:38,992 --> 00:42:41,703
I should be the one
apologizing to you, Momay.

436
00:42:44,216 --> 00:42:48,233
Because I believed you were
capable of hurting yourself.

437
00:42:58,415 --> 00:43:00,625
You didn’t do anything wrong, Mom.

438
00:43:04,701 --> 00:43:06,584
I love you so much, Momay.

439
00:43:10,915 --> 00:43:19,556
My only wish as your mom
is for you to rest in peace.

440
00:43:25,472 --> 00:43:27,348
I love you too, Mom.

441
00:43:33,685 --> 00:43:37,147
I’m happy, Mom, that in this life,

442
00:43:37,812 --> 00:43:41,775
your voice is the first
and last I’ll ever hear.

443
00:43:58,792 --> 00:44:00,585
Hi, Felice.

444
00:44:18,948 --> 00:44:22,201
Everything’s a blur about
what happened that night.

445
00:44:23,999 --> 00:44:26,168
But I was left with evidence.

446
00:44:26,168 --> 00:44:27,502
You killed her.

447
00:44:27,502 --> 00:44:29,629
Okay, fine. I killed her.

448
00:44:31,131 --> 00:44:33,967
Proof of what truly happened.

449
00:44:36,178 --> 00:44:37,762
Don’t worry, Momay.

450
00:44:39,491 --> 00:44:41,409
I’ll take care of your mom.

451
00:44:43,431 --> 00:44:45,350
I won’t abandon her.

452
00:44:58,569 --> 00:44:59,780
Finally.

453
00:45:00,296 --> 00:45:02,715
I can say my heart is at peace.

454
00:45:03,675 --> 00:45:06,094
Everything's going to be alright.

455
00:45:07,679 --> 00:45:09,037
Thanks to Felice,

456
00:45:09,597 --> 00:45:14,394
my name was cleared
about the stealing allegations.

457
00:45:15,210 --> 00:45:17,545
Naomi was given a sanction.

458
00:45:19,100 --> 00:45:21,587
Now everyone knows I didn't commit suicide.

459
00:45:22,485 --> 00:45:24,028
I'm a victim.

460
00:45:25,409 --> 00:45:27,786
The true monster is Dylan Gallego.

461
00:45:29,593 --> 00:45:31,261
Even if I didn't kill him,

462
00:45:31,709 --> 00:45:34,530
he still ended up in prison
and will be held accountable by the law.

463
00:45:37,507 --> 00:45:40,529
And now I know that
even when I’m gone,

464
00:45:41,015 --> 00:45:43,997
there will still be someone to
love the people I left behind.

465
00:45:45,085 --> 00:45:48,371
That is enough for me to say
that I am ready to let go.
